==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*σκάνδαλον / skandalon / skan'-dal-on

===Etymology===
*A “[[scandal]]”; probably from a derivative of [[κάμπτω]]; a trap stick (bent sapling), that is, [[snare]] (figuratively cause of displeasure or sin): 

===Noun===
'''σκάνδαλον'''

# An occasion to fall (of stumbling), [[offence]], thing that offends, stumbling-block.

